Introduction: This will be a technical specification for a game with the design of mirrors edge meets trackmania with grappling hook and time related powerups. The design gave mirrors edge and trackmania as examples, cyberpunk visuals, and powerups. 

I have added design of how gameplay could work:The game will be as drawn above with gaps, short walls, high walls, and side walls. The actions the character can take are the parkour moves of  jumping, vaultinig, and tic tac. Jumping will be used to cross gaps and jup over short walls, vaulting will be used to cross short walls quickly, and tic tac will be used to kick off walls implemented by temporary, invisible platforms. The goal will be to make it throught the course in as little time as possible. The powerups are timeslow, JumpDash, and grapplingHook. Timeslow temporarily makes it easier to jump off walls and slows your runtime. Jampdash is a fast mostly horizontal movement that is periodically available. Grappling hook is a fast mostly verical movement that is periodically available. The light lines signify places where the player can switch paths. The blue lines are the path the player must take to cross obstacles. The red numbers are estimated time required for different tasks. The purple lines are for helping visulize how the platforms are stored.

Platform: This will be a webb aplication built by the playCanvas 3d Game engine and coded with js

Game Manager

- Variables  
  - Run time: int \- Tracks time length of run  
  - Leaderboard: List\<int\> \- Shows top 20 Run times  
  - Player: Player \- instance of playable character  
  - gameOver: Boolean \- tracks if finish line reached  
  - Course: Course \- instance of a collection of paths and obstacles  
  - HUD: HUD displayed runtime and leaderboard  
  - Cameria: cameria \- controls player view  
- Methods  
  - Start game \- initalizes player, and runtime  
  - finish game \- updates database with runtime  
  - updateHUD \- updates HUD with runtimes  
  - updateCamera \- maintains 3rd person perspective of player  
  - Die \- resets run time and player position

Player

- Variables  
  - Direction: int \- gets direction of player view  
  - Position: List\<int\> \- gets 3d position of player (x,y,z)  
  - Speed: int \- controls player rate of movement  
  - Jump force: int \- decidses vertical force of jump  
  - JumpDash reload (speed boost): int \- time between available JumpDashes  
  - isVaulting: boolean \- checks if player is in vaulting state  
  - PowerUpType: bool {timeSlow || GrapplingHook} \- tracks what power the player has  
  - Gravity: int \- decides players downwards acceleration  
- Methods  
  - Move \- updates position based on direction and gravity  
  - Jump \- updates vertical position based on jumpforce, and gravity  
  - Vault \- updates playerstate temporarily  
  - JumpDach \-makes the player do a long quick jump (jump, decrease gravity, and move)  
  - Change view \- changes what the player is seeing based on mouse position (5 options)  
  - GrapplingHook \- removes need for wall run over high walls  
  - Timeslow: subtract 0.25 seconds from runtime for 5 seconds \+ extend temp platform duration by 1 second

Course

- Paths \- a 4 by 14 2d array that contains T or F to represent if a platform exits in the space  
  - Variables  
    - IsEmpty \- returns true if F is in the array  
  - Methids  
    - detectCollision  
      - If is empty then call die  
      - Else supports the player  
- Obstacles  
  - Variables  
    - isLowWall: boolean  
    - isHighWall: boolean  
    - isSideWall: boolean  
  - Methods  
    - Temp platform \- if isHighWall || isSideWall gives player a temporary “platform”  
    - detectCollision   
      - if isLowWall   
        - if vaulting ignorewall   
        - else if jumping ignore wall then stop   
        - else stop  
      - Else  
        - Temp platform
